 Since $a^3 = x^3 - 3x$ and $b^3 = x^3 - 5,$ $a^3 - b^3 = x^3 - 3x - 5.$  Since $a$ and $b$ are roots of $x^3 - 3x - 5 = 0,$ $a^3 - b^3 = 0.$  Therefore, $a = b = \boxed{3}.$

[asy]
size(3cm);

pair a, b, c;

a = (0, -2); b = (1, -1); c = (2, 0);

draw(a--b--c, red);

label("$x$", a, SW);
label("$y$", b, NW);
label("$z$", c, NE);

dot(a, b, red);
dot(b, c, red);
dot(c, a, red);

dot(a, b, "--", 3);
dot(b, c, "--", 3);
dot(c, a, "--", 3);

dot(a, b, "", 3);
dot(b, c, "", 3);
dot(c, a, "", 3);

dot(a, b, "x", 3);
dot(b, c, "y", 3);
dot(c, a, "z", 3);

label("$x^3 - 3x - 5 = 0$", a, SW);
[/asy]
